Local modifications to upstream
-------------------------------
The following one-line bug fix has been applied on top of the vendored
sources. It should be sent upstream as a PR.

* `scripts/build_deck.py` (around line 970, in `build_slide`):
  Replaced `if idx in slide.placeholders: ph = slide.placeholders[idx]`
  with a `try / except KeyError` around `slide.placeholders[idx]`.

  Rationale: `pptx.shapes.shapetree.SlidePlaceholders` does not implement
  `__contains__`, so `int in slide.placeholders` always evaluates to
  `False` (Python falls back to iterating shape objects and comparing
  them to the int). The result upstream is that `placeholders:` entries
  in `content.yaml` are silently dropped — every layout-bound title /
  body comes out blank. The `try/except` matches the documented
  semantics of `__getitem__`, which raises `KeyError` when no
  placeholder with that idx exists.

